# CervixAI Business Requirements Document

---

## Executive Summary

CervixAI is an AI-powered clinical diagnostic platform designed to revolutionize cervical cancer screening, diagnosis, and longitudinal patient monitoring by seamlessly integrating AI algorithms with mandatory human oversight. It leverages a scalable vertical architecture and an episode-based design to ensure continuity of care and prevent fragmented diagnostic workflows. The platform prioritizes explainability via heatmaps and audit trails, addresses data scarcity through synthetic augmentation, and maintains a vendor-neutral posture to integrate smoothly with existing hospital infrastructure. Surgically positioned for US and EU markets with plans for expansion into low-resource regions, CervixAI is architected under a secure, hybrid zero-trust framework and complies with rigorous regulatory standards including HIPAA, GDPR, FDA SaMD guidance, and ISO quality and safety norms. The business aims to achieve clinical excellence, demonstrated by ≥95% sensitivity, significant pathologist workload reduction, and sustained social impact through democratized diagnostic access.

