## Risk Analysis and Mitigation Strategies

| Risk                     | Impact            | Likelihood | Mitigation Strategy                                                                                      |
|--------------------------|-------------------|------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| AI diagnostic errors     | High (patient harm)| Medium     | Mandatory human oversight; continuous model validation and retraining; bias monitoring protocols        |
| Data breaches            | High              | Low        | Zero-trust architecture; encryption; intrusion detection; strict access controls and audit mechanisms   |
| Regulatory non-compliance| High              | Low-Med    | Comprehensive QMS; expert regulatory engagement; documentation rigor; preemptive audits                 |
| Integration failures     | Medium            | Medium     | Vendor-neutral design; modular API contracts; phased deployment with hospital IT collaboration           |
| User resistance          | Medium            | Medium     | Extensive training, explainable AI features, clinician input loops, pilot proof of clinical benefit       |
| Infrastructure downtime  | High              | Low        | Kubernetes HA clusters; automated monitoring; disaster recovery plans; multi-region failover             |

