# Appendix: Summary of Architecture and Deployment

- Hybrid zero-trust security model segregates clinical on-premise tools from cloud infrastructure using micro-segmentation, mutual TLS, and federated identity management.
- Multi-tiered data architecture stores patient records (structured registries), images (object/PACS storage), and AI embeddings (semantic vector search) linked cohesively.
- Kubernetes orchestrates containerized AI agents and services providing scalability, resilience, dynamic resource allocation, and continuous monitoring.
- Automated monitoring and disaster recovery subsystems ensure real-time observability, alert escalation, and rapid recovery with tested backup and failover plans.
- Vendor-neutral interfaces based on FHIR, HL7, and DICOM standards enable smooth integration into heterogeneous hospital IT environments.

